nodes.name: help menu

embedfields.name: purge
embedfields.value: Deletes # of messages stated after the command Ex: ${tempVars.prefix}purge 50

embedfields.name: pfp
embedfields.value: Gets the profile picture of whoever mentioned

embedfields.name: giverole
embedfields.value: Gives the role to whoever mentioned, used like this: ${tempVars.prefix}giverole @user (rolename) Ex: ${tempVars.prefix}giverole @fuckstick DUMB FUCK (HAS TO BE AN EXISTING ROLE)

embedfields.name: removerole
embedfields.value: Removes the role of whoever mentioned. Ex: ${tempVars.prefix}removerole @fuckstick DUMB FUCK

embedfields.name: slowmode
embedfields.value: Sets slowmode to the amount of seconds after the command Ex: ${tempVars.prefix}slowmode 5

embedfields.name: uptime
embedfields.value: Shows how long the bot has been online

embedfields.name: default role
embedfields.value: The role added on join of a new member. ${tempVars.prefix}defaultrole (rolename) Ex. ${tempVars.prefix}defaultrole FUCKSTICK

embedfields.name: default channel
embedfields.value: The channel where joins, kicks, and bans are sent. ${tempVars.prefix}defaultchannel (channel name) Ex: ${tempVars.prefix}defaultchannel welcomes-leaves

embedfields.name: muterole
embedfields.value:
Sets the role that is given when using the mute command 
${tempVars.prefix}muterole (rolename) Ex: ${tempVars.prefix}muterole muted

embedfields.name: invite
embedfields.value: Gets an invite link so you can invite the bot to your own server

embedfields.name: console channel
embedfields.value: Sets the channel to be used as the bots' console, where all commands used by the users are logged Ex: ${tempVars.prefix}consolechannel bot-logs

embedfields.name: prefix
embedfields.value: Sets the prefix of the server. Make sure to remember this
